er\"\n! [[1953 12 Hours of Reims|1953]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Hersham and Walton Motors|H.W. Motors]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{Flagicon|Belgium}} [[Paul Fr\u00e8re]]\n|align=\"left\"| [[Hersham and Walton Motors|HWM-Jaguar]]\n| S+2.0\n| \n| colspan=2|DNF<br>(Suspension)\n|- align=\"center\"\n! [[1954 12 Hours of Reims|1954]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Hersham and Walton Motors|H.W. Motors]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Lance Macklin]]\n|align=\"left\"| [[Hersham and Walton Motors|HWM-Jaguar]]\n| S+2.0\n| \n| colspan=2|DNF<br>(Engine)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|}\n\n===Complete 12 Hours of Hy\u00e8res results===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Team\n! Co-Drivers\n! Car\n! Class\n! Laps\n! {{Tooltip|Pos.|Overall Position}}\n! {{Tooltip|Class<br>Pos.|Class Position}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n! [[1954 12 Hours of Hy\u00e8res|1954]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Hersham and Walton Motors|H.W. Motors]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{Flagicon|Australia}} [[Tony Gaze (racing driver)|Tony Gaze]]\n|align=\"left\"| [[Hersham and Walton Motors|HWM-Jaguar]]\n|\n| \n| colspan=2|DISQ<br>(Disqualified)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book |first=David |last=Abecassis |title=A Passion for Speed: the life and times of George Abecassis |publisher=P J Publishing |location= |year=2010 |isbn=978-0-9550102-6-2 }}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170407141748/http://www.georgeabecassis.com/ George Abecassis Racing Driver with a Passion for Speed] (georgeabecassis.com), 2010.\n* [http://www.hwm.co.uk/our-history Our History], HWM of Walton on Thames, West London.\n* ''[http://www.motorsportmagazine.com/archive/article/august-1958/28/fast-motoring-facel-vega Fast motoring in a Facel Vega],'', [[Motor Sport Magazine]], August 1958.\n* {{cite web |url=https://www.tracesofwar.com/persons/39028/Abecassis-George-Edgar.htm |title=Abecassis, George Edgar |work=Traces of 